title: Strata SE1
description:
Strata SE1 is a residential skyscraper at Elephant and Castle in the London Borough of Southwark. Designed by BFLS, it was constructed from 2007 to 2010 at a cost of £113,000,000. The building, with 43 floors, has a height of 148 m (486 ft) and a floor area of 23,690 sq m (255,000 sq ft). The tower contains 400 residential flats. It is equipped with 4 lifts. The top of Strata SE1 incorporates three wind turbines.

http://www.skyscrapernews.com/buildings.php?id=4488

title: Denmark Hill Railway Station
description:
Denmark Hill railway station is a railway station in the London Borough of Southwark in London, England, on the South London Line. The station is managed by Southeastern and is served by trains of that company and Southern. It is in Travelcard Zone 2. It is located on Champion Park in the south of Camberwell, in an area known as Denmark Hill. It is near to the King's College and Maudsley hospitals. The station is mostly served by local trains from three London terminus stations: London Bridge, Victoria and Blackfriars, although some services are under threat of closure.

Windsor Walk
London
SE5 8BB

title: St Mary Magdalen Church, Bermondsey
description:
The medieval parish church of Bermondsey, built alongside Bermondsey Abbey.   It was rebuilt in the 17th century with later "gothick" details on the tower.  There is a surviving parish watch house and the adjoining churchyard is now a public park.
The church building is a Grade II* listed building.
http://www.stmarysbermondsey.org.uk
